My 8:00 class got cancelled today and I have nothing to do till 10 so I guess I will just blog. lol 

College has been pretty cool so far... everybody seems to be really friendly here. My floormates are pretty chill, but the guys on the floor are a bunch A holes. lol long story I guess, or more like too lazy to go into detail...... But for sure, someone's gonna get it on April's Fools day . heh heh heh.... suckers.

Hmmm, what else? I have a shitload of flyers and papers to random events stashed in my drawer because every day me, Erica, and Kim get bombarded / harassed by all these clubs and sororities....... still not really sure if I want to join anything yet (it's a big commitmen), but still keeping my options open. 

I basically ride my bike every where, or walk, or call George 'cause he has a car. haha I'm sorta getting use to where everything is... but If you ever asked me for directions before you know that my sense of direction is TERRIBLE..... But I'm getting better! 

The food here is "deese" (that's Central Cal for "decent" :-) ), it keeps me alive, haha. I went to go eat pho the other day with Erica Kim Cat Jaq and George. Everybody in there was white, haha. Then afterwards we went to go watch "Cloudy Meatballs" . entertaining stuff


That's it for now, I guess. ran out of things to talk about... I'll update whenever I update lol. I got a feeling I will just neglect this blog till the next time my class gets cancelled, har har har. kk going to get ready to crash Chinese 1 in a lil bit, hope I get in. I miss you guys! (whoever's reading this....) and I hope you're having fun at your school too. Call me on my cellular, I love random phone calls. :-) they make my day .
Hang with the bro Thursday night. Santana Row Friday night. Then bowling at Mission Lanes and Sierra Mts. Pt. 2 . Perfect end to a chapter, in my opinion. :-)

Can you believe it? 'cause I can't. 

But I've never been more ready in my life. Let the good times rolllllll! ;)

Ball. Tag. In-N-Out. Met up with Matt and Richard at Brian Tran's. Sierra Mountains. soooo amazing!! very glad we went. I got such an incredible feeling when I looked out on to the city. <3 Next day: last day of work!, Yogurt Twist, Cathy's, almost got killed on the way there (my fault.... :[), and Walmart.
My-Van pretended to throw a can of soup at me today. Naturally, I freaked out and almost took out an entire shelf of laundry detergent. Good times..

Movie night with Meeves and TC. Yummm, pizza! :-) Early morning wake up call the next day. OMG..... I wanted to curl up in a ball and die, lol. So early! They saw my messy room too. :-( We went Target shopping, and I bought bedsheets. Then G mall where I bought a wooden baseball bat (for protection, NOT "slutty baseball outfit"...... ). Ate disgusting pad thai and vegetables at food court... Then West Valley to watch a water polo  game. Then Pinkberry for yogurt at Santana Row. Then Indy for bike pick-up. Then Target again to return something. Then home. Woo, pooped. Work tomorrow at 6 with Meeves. oh joy..... but at least this time I've got company. :-)

Work, sleep, party. Then played hooky the next day. :P So bad......

 
NOTE TO SELF: Do NOT attempt to chug two of these in less than 30 seconds. holy fuck...... i was jittery as HELLL!!! had no idea... shit is strong!!

(Can't sleep.) Signed up for classes today online. My-Van tried to help me, but I was sorta being too picky lol. Ended up with...... Academic Writing, Religious Practice and the State in China, and Statistics. Went to Yogurt Twist afterwards with Matt, Richard, and Van-anh and hung out with them for a good 15 minutes lol, then left. Went home where hell ensued. Got work in 4 hours. not looking forward to waking up....

BBQ @ Tanya's. iHop with Tracy, Chris, Cathy, Peter, and Steven. OMG, got scared silly in the car! I screamed so loud that my throat started hurting after.. I'm going to get you guys back, watch.. STEVEN. Tired. Night!

Valley Fair with Tracy and Diana. Bought a snake-print halter from Express. Sssss.. Ssss.... SLYTHERIN..... (that's the sound of me trying to be a snake ;) ) Visited Urban Outfitters, then home. Might go out later again to Steven's to watch Tracy cook Viet food.. and then possible Cranium pt. 2?? :-)

Tell an Aquarius to do one thing and she'll do just the opposite. You are laughing as you read this because you know it's true. That's your role as the zodiac's rabble-rouser-to turn things upside down and inside out. Don't ever change. Aquarians are fascinating creatures and are often in the media, making news in fashion, politics, community work, or for charities. Brimming with self-confidence, you love bright, neon colors or anything that looks futuristic.

+ +   + = best halloween EVER!!!

Ahhh, so stoked. Can't wait. :-)

Literally, a very silly question to ask... but metaphorically, deep. Deep like the ocean.

Sometimes I feel like I'm an emotionless droid or something, just going through the motions of life. Other times I feel like life is like a movie screen, and I'm just sitting back and watching everything play out in front of me-- watching time past me by as I'm set on this proverbial cruise control...

I don't know if this is a good or a bad thing? 'cause you know what they say:  something something.... hold it too tight you'll crush it, but if you hold it too loose it'll get away.. or some shit like that, idk. But the point is..... I think I'm letting life slip through my hands and not really taking initiative towards anything really. Maybe it's just the situation I am in now that makes me feel this way.. but either way, I feel that I should be doing something productive with my life.

In the 18 years I have been alive, I cannot say with confidence that I have made any small or miniscule impact on this world at all, except maybe terrorizing the ones around me. I sure hope I can find something to fill this void in me at Santa Barbara, or at least some sort of activity that will make me feel semi-human because I DON'T want to be a robot.....

I wish I was better with words... I noticed that not a lot of my posts really have much depth to them. Most of them are simply about my day, etc. or random tidbits that I find on the web (youtube videos, funny pictures)... Not to say that there's anything wrong with that, just that I wished I had more to offer than just "So TODAY I went to blahdeblah.... and I bought yadayada....." or "Hey! Check out this funny video of this guy getting face planted into a wall!"
I think writing is amazing, especially if you're good at it. Some people just have a gift of putting their feelings and thoughts into these perfectly poised and structured sentences that offer so much insight and just make you go "Hmmmm."
I also really admire people that document their days in pictures. I could probably never pull it off though because, well... (1) I totally SUCK at taking pictures, (2) My piece of shit camera is a piece of shit, and (3) Unless you want to see 50 pictures of me sitting at home, in front of my computer, my life really isn't all that interesting.

Hmmm not much to update  about... just wanted to post something.
Oh, I had a job interview today. Hope I get it! but not really holding my breath..
Hope everyone is having a wonderful summer! :-)

I recently rediscovered the Yeah Yeah Yeahs. I use to listen to them way back when in middle school when me and Jacqueline use to be "siamese twins" and we dressed in black and white ( our school had uniforms) and we use to go to Target after school every day to steal their coffee creamers. LOL Man, those were the days. :-)

Today was the Senior Farewell Assembly..... it still hasn't really hit me yet that I'm actually graduating. Weird. 
Next week will be my last week of high school. Hmmm will I miss it? Yes. No. Maybe so. idk
There are some things that I love, like the people, but there are also some things I really hate, like the drama... 
But I think all in all, high school has been a pretty fun experience for me. 
I'd like to think that I've grown as a person... but I still can be really shy/ awkward sometimes. lol Hmm I guess that's just the kind of person I am? idk
But I definitely want to live it up this summer before I go to college with some old and also new friends. 
I can't wait to start my new life in Santa Barbara with my homie G, Erica Ye. lol We're gonna have a blasttttt!

Well, this is just a short reflection post I guess. Not really much to say... just can't wait for summer to begin. WOOT WOOT! Class of '09!

oh yea, P.S. prom was fuuun! lol At first I was kinda like ehh, but now that I think back on it I had a great time and I had the best date ever! I would love to just do it all over again. :-)
